title: Ground News - Stolen donation truck returned to Tacoma Habitat for Humanity
text:
Summary by Ground News A stolen donation truck was returned to the Tacoma /Pierce County Habitat for Humanity. Authorities received a tip from someone about a truck that matched the description of the stolen vehicle. The truck was discovered nearly an hour north of Tacoma in a Redmond neighborhood. There was no major damage, but the license plates had been swapped with temporary ones. Share menu More
